quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  33,7,"And recall that We took from the prophets their pledge, and from you<sup>sg </sup>and from Noah and Abraham and Moses and Jesus, son of Mary, and We took from them a solid pledge,"
  33,8,"that He{1}may ask the truthful{2}about their truthfulness. Yet He has prepared for the deniers a painful punishment.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from 1<sup><small>st</small></sup> person to 3<sup><small>rd</small></sup> person.],footnotes:2:[On the Day of Judgment.]
  33,9,"O you who have attained faith, remember Allah’s blessings upon you when troops advanced towards you, and We{1}sent against them a wind and troops that you did not see. And Allah has always been All-Seeing of what you do{2}.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from 3<sup><small>rd</small></sup>rd person to 1<sup><small>st</small></sup>st person],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Abu Amr read it as: “…of what they do.”]
  33,10,"When they came upon you<sup>pl </sup>from above you and from beneath you, and when sight<i>(s) </i>swerved and hearts reached the larynges, and you assume{1}about Allah various assumptions.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense, which serves to create a vivid portrait of past events.]
